-- Russia’s ru-Net Invests in Turkish E-commerce Startup Lidyana
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-06-28T07:40:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/russia-s-ru-net-invests-in-turkish-e-commerce-startup-lidyana.html
Russia ’s ru-Net has invested 6
million liras ($3.3 million) in Lidyana.com, a Turkish firm that
sells jewelry and accessories over the internet, according to an
e-mailed statement from Lidyana today.  The investment will be used to help the Istanbul-based
company to expand operations into Russia and the  Middle East ,
Chief Executive Officer Hakan Bas said in the statement.  Lidyana includes Turkish national soccer team player Arda
Turan, flash sales site Markafoni.com founders Sina Afra, Tolga
Tatari and Ahmet Sari, and food delivery site Yemeksepeti.com
founder Nevzat Aydin among its partners, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
